Tony Narlock's scrot wm configuration (http://github.com/tony)

Version: scrotwm 0.9.23

For use with conky-cli (Conky compiled without X)

Includes conky command line file. The conky script included will work with mpd (music player daemon) and your cpu/mem stats.



Font info:

  ArchLinux:
  # pacman -S terminus-font

  Then go to vim /etc/X11/xorg.conf and add your font dir to be scanned:

  Section "Files"
    FontPath     "/usr/share/fonts/local"
  EndSection

  Ubuntu:
  # sudo apt-get install xfonts-terminus


